Comment (src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue:604):
**[Low / perf] `loadCatalogControlTitles` fetches every catalog's `/full`, much of it redundant.** This lists all catalogs and then fans out a `/full` request per catalog just to build a controlId→title map. On an instance with several large catalogs (e.g. full 800-53) that's a lot of payload on every visit to the suggestions page. Note the profile resolution you already do (`/resolved-with-catalogs`) returns `title` per control too, so for controls in a bound profile the catalog fetch is duplicate work. Non-blocking, but consider: prefer the profile-resolved titles and only fall back to catalogs for controls still missing a title, and/or scope the catalog fetch to the catalog(s) actually referenced by this SSP/its profiles rather than all of them.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** In src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue, optimize loadCatalogControlTitles so the suggestions page does not fetch every catalog /full just to build control titles. Reuse the titles already available from the bound profile resolved-with-catalogs responses when building the controlId-to-title map for controlOptions. After profile resolution completes, compute which implementedRequirement.controlId values still lack a title, and only then fall back to catalog data for those missing controls. If the app exposes catalog ids through the resolved profile/catalog metadata, fetch only those referenced catalogs; otherwise keep the fallback guarded so it stops once all implemented controls have titles and does not fan out all catalogs unnecessarily. Preserve the existing controlId-only fallback when title lookup fails, and do not change option.value or the generate payload.

